# Performance Discipline

Default reflex for heavy or interactive work. Workspace profiling tools and `perf_targets.json` layout live in project `performance.instructions.md`.

## When This Applies

| Surface | Perf reflex required? |
|---|---|
| Interactive UI (paint, viewport, canvas, drag/zoom/scroll) | **Yes** — strict frame budget |
| Fullscreen/large-area UI fills | **Yes** — GPU-first + strict frame budget |
| Batch processing (compression, ML, large file ops) | **Yes** — throughput + log |
| One-shot CLI on small inputs | No (unless user reports slowness) |
| Pure CRUD / config / parsing | No |

If it loops over user-scale data or runs on a frame timer → yes.

## Default Budgets

| Surface | p95 budget |
|---|---|
| Frame-based interactive (stroke, pan/zoom, orbit) | 16.6 ms / frame (60 FPS) |
| Discrete UI response (click → feedback) | ≤100 ms |
| GPU compute dispatch per call | ≤8 ms |
| Batch op per item | declared per task |
| Module init / first-paint | ≤500 ms |

Declare explicit budgets for surfaces that need different targets.

## Optimization Escalation Ladder

Walk in order. Stop at the first rung that hits budget. **Do not skip rungs.**

| # | Technique | When |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Don't redraw / recompute (`dirty_rect`, memoize per-input) | Always |
| 2 | Cull off-screen / out-of-scope work | >100 items |
| 3 | LOD / mip / batch summarize when zoomed out | Tile/streaming |
| 4 | Move work to GPU | CPU-bound, parallelizable |
| 5 | Throttle / coalesce events (one-per-frame, debounce) | Handlers >60Hz |
| 6 | Async / background prep | Large I/O, tile gen |
| 7 | Cross-frame cache with explicit invalidation key | Last resort |

## Cross-Frame Cache Discipline (Rung 7)

| Rule | Why |
|---|---|
| Cache MUST have explicit `key` tuple of all inputs | Forgotten invalidation is the #1 cache bug |
| Key includes data version, viewport, zoom, rotation, theme generation, DPR | Known footguns |
| Only `get_or_build(key, builder)` — no separate `set()` | Forces contract |
| Overlays (cursor, selection) NOT cached | Prevents smear |

## GPU-First on Interactive Surfaces

Use GPU dispatch/rendering from day one when available. CPU fallback only for tiny inputs, headless tests, export, or validated reference paths.

Do not ship CPU-only "for now" planning to GPU-port later.

## Perf Log Verdict (machine-checkable)

| p95 vs budget | Verdict |
|---|---|
| `> budget` | `fail` |
| `0.8 * budget < p95 ≤ budget` | `warn` |
| `≤ 0.8 * budget` | `ok` |

Read structured perf JSON and act on `overall_verdict` before declaring work complete.

## Bottom-Up Composition Isolation

When timers cannot localize cost: measure primitives in isolation, add one at a time, watch interaction cliffs; compare host wrapper variants (`QOpenGLWidget` vs `QOpenGLWindow`, embedded vs standalone).

## Qt / Windows Render Surface Gotchas

Check early when Qt+OpenGL stalls at ~30 FPS on Windows: `QOpenGLWidget` FBO compositing vs `QOpenGLWindow` + `createWindowContainer`; default `QTimer` 15.6 ms resolution; DWM VSync waits.

## Anti-Patterns

- ❌ Measure by feel — use budgets and logs
- ❌ Cache before walking rungs 1–6
- ❌ Cache without explicit key dataclass
- ❌ Raw `time.perf_counter()` sprinkles in production
- ❌ Optimizing one host wrapper when another with identical content is fast
